  "storyTitle": "Kong Rong Shares the Pears",
  "summary": "As a child, Kong Rong chose the smaller pear and yielded the bigger pears to his older brothers, showing courtesy and respect.",
  "storyPlot": "When Kong Rong was a child, pears were being shared among the children at home. Some pears were big and some were small. Instead of reaching for the biggest one, Kong Rong willingly chose a small pear. When the adults asked why, he said that he was younger and should take the smaller one, while the bigger pears should go to his older brothers. The story is often used to teach courtesy, restraint, and the habit of thinking of others before oneself.",
